The paper discusses the integration of a DBMS with a distributed file system for transaction processing of big data. This topic falls under the category of database systems and distributed computing, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.DB, cs.DC, and cs.DS. The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed architecture and the efficient transaction management method, which falls under the category of software engineering, covered by the sub-category cs.SE. Finally, the paper discusses the scalability and reliability of the proposed system, which is a key aspect of distributed and parallel computing, covered by the sub-category cs.Distributed and Parallel Computing.
